Another couple days gap between DAY05 and DAY06 but I grinded out my case design today. I decided to use Onshape instead of Fusion360 because the Onshape is completely free. Designing the case was the most challenging yet
fun part of the project for me so far. I mostly used guides to figure out how tools work in Onshape and then I would take breaks to think about how I could use certain tools to help me make a certain part in my case design.
It may sound like I am overexaggerating the design process but it honestly was that fun for me; I got to use math and critical thinking to ensure my measurements were correct! Honestly, Onshape is still pretty frustrating as
some tools feel like they function unpredictably, like the coincident tool which would sometimes snap my circle to a line before I could choose to attach it to the midpoint (no matter what order I selected them in). I'm not
going to submit my project until DAY07 since I want some time for my project to "marinate" so I can see if I want to make any last minute changes or if I realize there might be a concern with a design I made. The plan for
DAY07 is to finish the firmware and submit the project!
